oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: First train in Crossville
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of a railroad and train in Crossville, Tennessee which was part of the Tennessee Central Railway and the first train in Crossville. Shows buildings and a large crowd of people. Written on photograph, "First train to Crossville."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Railroads; Railroad tracks; Railroad locomotives
